We run BiocCheckGitClone on a raw clone of the github directory.   If you are running it locally and had .gitignored those files before pushing to github then you should be okay.   A way to test this would be to do a git clone  of your github repository, in a different, temporary location to see if those files are still present when you do a git clone and running BiocCheckGitClone on that temporary cloned copy.

